if fetch_api.call() is used (by javascript), 
it will return a promise that resolves to the response of the request. 
If not used, it will return an error indicating that fetch_api is not defined.

+

avoids reloading the page after deleting a todo item, 
which can be inefficient and may cause the user to lose their place in the list. 
Instead, you can use JavaScript to remove the deleted item from the DOM without reloading the page.